# Capstone Project – Sprint 0

## Project Overview
**Project Name:** Group Formation App  
**Product Name:** Groupify  
**Group Name:** The Survivors  

Groupify is a web-based application that enables users to form groups within a shared workspace, communicate effectively, and manage tasks efficiently. The platform is designed to support collaborative environments such as academic courses, hackathons, workplaces, and personal projects.

This repository contains the source code, documentation, and resources for **Team 12’s Capstone Project**. Sprint 0 focuses on understanding the project domain, defining requirements, and setting up foundational tools.

---

## Project Description
Groupify allows users to create or join workspaces, build profiles highlighting their skills and availability, and form groups based on project needs. The system supports user authentication, role-based access, real-time communication, and task planning. An AI-assisted feature helps suggest optimal group members based on skills and other criteria.

---

## Key Features
- User login and signup
- Role-based access control
- Workspace creation and management
- User profiles with skills and availability
- Group creation and management
- AI-assisted member suggestion based on skills
- Group chat
- Task planner with per-task comment threads

---

## Sprint 0 Objectives
- Understand the project problem and scope
- Identify stakeholders and target users
- Gather functional and non-functional requirements
- Define initial user personas
- Establish project management and version control tools
- Create initial planning artifacts (Trello, Project Charter)

